ProtoDefines:
. "We call a nonzero rational number $n$ a \term{ congruent 
   number} if $\pm n$ is the area of a right triangle with 
   rational side lengths. Equivalently, $n$ is a \term{ congruent
   number} if the system of two equations \begin{eqnarray*} 
   a^2+b^2&=&c^2\\ \frac{1}{2}ab&=&n \end{eqnarray*} has a 
   solution with $a,b,c\in\mathbf{Q}$."
